  "commentary": "With SPX spot at 6589.95 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6590 and having broken through a gamma wall, dealers are likely providing modest buying support as they're long gamma in this PIN regime. The massive positive gamma wall at 6600 (+73.2B) should act as strong resistance where dealers will aggressively sell any rallies, while the negative gamma pocket at 6560 (-6.3B) represents the key downside level where dealer buying accelerates. Given the stabilizing regime and proximity to the flip point, expect range-bound action between 6560-6600 with dealers providing liquidity on both sides.\n\nBottom line: expect choppy trading with resistance near 6600 and support around 6560.",
